Mouchel Open to Offers, Lenders Seek Advice on Profits, FT Says

-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 
2011-10-08T09:10:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-08/mouchel-open-to-offers-lenders-seek-advice-on-profits-ft-says.html
Mouchel Group Plc (MCHL) ’s board is open to
any serious takeover approach after shares in the company slid
following an accounting error that cut its profit, the Financial
Times  reported , citing a person it didn’t identify.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS) , Lloyds Banking Group Plc
and  Barclays Plc (BARC)  are to hire accounting firm KPMG LLP to advise
them on Mouchel’s earning, the newspaper said, citing people
with knowledge of the situation that it did not name.  Melanie Bright, a spokeswoman for the company, couldn’t
immediately comment when reached by phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Dobson in London at 
